==English==

===Etymology===
{{compound|chair|person|lang=en}}, after {{m|en|chairman}} and {{m|en|chairwoman}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|chairpeople}}

# a [[chairman]] or [[chairwoman]], someone who [[preside]]s over a [[meeting]], [[board]], etc.
#: ''She was the '''chairperson''' of the board and she [[preside]]d over the meeting''.

====Usage notes====
In modern usage, terms like {{m|en|chair}}, {{m|en|moderator}}, {{m|en|coordinator}}, {{m|en|presiding}} {{m|en|officer}}, {{m|en|group}} {{m|en|leader}}, {{m|en|head}}, {{m|en|facilitator}}, and so forth, are often preferred.

====Synonyms====
* {{l|en|chair}}
* {{l|en|presiding}} [[officer]], [[presider]]

